I'll convert the dependencies in MainActivity to use singletons instead of creating new instances each time. This will ensure we have only one instance of each dependency throughout the app.

```kotlin:app/src/main/java/com/githubrepofinder/ui/MainActivity.kt
 override fun onCreate(savedInstanceState: Bundle?) {
 super.onCreate(savedInstanceState)
 binding = ActivityMainBinding.inflate(layoutInflater)
 setContentView(binding.root)

 // Initialize dependencies using singletons
 val database = AppDatabase.getInstance(applicationContext)
 val repoDao = database.repoDao()
 val networkService = NetworkService.getInstance()
 val cacher = Cacher.getInstance(repoDao)
 val repository = GitHubRepository.getInstance(networkService, cacher)

 // Initialize ViewModel
 viewModel = ViewModelProvider(this, RepositoryViewModel.Factory(repository))[RepositoryViewModel::class.java]

 // Setup RecyclerView and Adapter
 setupRecyclerView()

 // ... existing code ...
```

You'll need to update the corresponding classes to implement the singleton pattern. Here's how to modify them:

1. For `AppDatabase.kt`, replace `getDatabase` with `getInstance`:
```kotlin
companion object {
 @Volatile
 private var INSTANCE: AppDatabase? = null

 fun getInstance(context: Context): AppDatabase {
 return INSTANCE ?: synchronized(this) {
 val instance = Room.databaseBuilder(
 context.applicationContext,
 AppDatabase::class.java,
 "app_database"
 ).build()
 INSTANCE = instance
 instance
 }
 }
}
```

2. For `NetworkService.kt`:
```kotlin
class NetworkService private constructor() {
 // existing implementation

 companion object {
 @Volatile
 private var INSTANCE: NetworkService? = null

 fun getInstance(): NetworkService {
 return INSTANCE ?: synchronized(this) {
 val instance = NetworkService()
 INSTANCE = instance
 instance
 }
 }
 }
}
```

3. For `Cacher.kt`:
```kotlin
class Cacher private constructor(private val repoDao: RepoDao) {
 // existing implementation

 companion object {
 @Volatile
 private var INSTANCE: Cacher? = null

 fun getInstance(repoDao: RepoDao): Cacher {
 return INSTANCE ?: synchronized(this) {
 val instance = Cacher(repoDao)
 INSTANCE = instance
 instance
 }
 }
 }
}
```

4. For `GitHubRepository.kt`:
```kotlin
class GitHubRepository private constructor(
 private val networkService: NetworkService,
 private val cacher: Cacher
) {
 // existing implementation

 companion object {
 @Volatile
 private var INSTANCE: GitHubRepository? = null

 fun getInstance(
 networkService: NetworkService,
 cacher: Cacher
 ): GitHubRepository {
 return INSTANCE ?: synchronized(this) {
 val instance = GitHubRepository(networkService, cacher)
 INSTANCE = instance
 instance
 }
 }
 }
}
```

This approach uses the double-checked locking pattern to ensure thread safety when creating the singleton instances."}]}

